data.text:
Tiger Tiger, first published in the United States in 1956 under the rather more impressive title The Stars My Destination is one of the two best known works of science fiction writer Alfred Bester.

In this pulse-quickening novel, Alfred Bester imagines a future in which people "jaunte" a thousand miles with a single thought, where the rich barricade themselves in labyrinths and protect themselves with radioactive hitmen—and where an inarticulate outcast is the most valuable and dangerous man alive.

_____________________________________________

Paperback, good condition. Some wear to cover edges. Previous owner's name inscribed.

Published by Penguin Books, 1979 (first published 1955).

ISBN: 0140026207
